{"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"bind","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketAddressT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"address","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"SocketAddressT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"allowReuse"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"extendedModule":"GIO","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:3GIO14SocketProtocolPAAE4bind7address10allowReuseSbqd___SbtKAA0b7AddressC0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO6SocketC","title":"bind(address:allowReuse:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method"},"abstract":[{"text":"When a socket is created it is attached to an address family, but it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t have an address in this family. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_bind()"},{"text":" assigns the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"address (sometimes called name) of the socket.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/bind(address:allowReuse:)"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"bind"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"SocketAddressT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"text":"address","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"SocketAddressT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"allowReuse","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"SocketAddressT"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketAddressProtocol","text":"SocketAddressProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO21SocketAddressProtocolP"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is generally required to bind to a local address before you can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"receive connections. (See ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_listen()"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_socket_accept()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ).","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In certain situations, you may also want to bind a socket that will be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"used to initiate connections, though this is not normally required."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"socket","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a TCP socket, then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"allowReuse"},{"type":"text","text":" controls the setting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the "},{"code":"SO_REUSEADDR","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" socket option; normally it should be ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"server sockets (sockets that you will eventually call","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_accept()"},{"text":" on), and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" for client sockets. (Failing to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"set this flag on a server socket may cause "},{"code":"g_socket_bind()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to return","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"addressInUse","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if the server program is stopped and then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"immediately restarted.)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"socket"},{"type":"text","text":" is a UDP socket, then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"allowReuse"},{"text":" determines whether or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not other UDP sockets can be bound to the same address at the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"time. In particular, you can have several UDP sockets bound to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"same address, and they will all receive all of the multicast and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"broadcast packets sent to that address. (The behavior of unicast"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"UDP packets to an address with multiple listeners is not defined.)"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/socket\/bind(address:allowreuse:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/SocketProtocol-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Socket":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Socket"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socket","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"GSocket","type":"codeVoice"},{"ty